---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import AdSlot from '../components/common/AdSlot.astro';

const termsSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'WebPage',
  'name': 'Terms & Conditions - ScribbleCraft Text to Handwriting',
  'description': 'Read the ScribbleCraft Terms and Conditions. Review rules on acceptable use, IP ownership, fraud prevention, and liability.'
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms & Conditions - Acceptable Use & Guidelines"
  description="Read the terms and conditions for using ScribbleCraft. Understand our strict anti-forgery rules, liability disclaimers, and content ownership policies."
  activeTab="terms"
  schema={termsSchema}
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-8">
    <AdSlot slotId="header-leaderboard" />

    <div class="border-b border-hairline pb-4 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-primary uppercase font-mono">Terms and Conditions</h1>
      <p class="text-xs text-mute font-mono mt-1">Effective Date: June 12, 2026. Please read these terms carefully before using our tools.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-xs md:text-sm text-body leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Welcome to ScribbleCraft (texttohandwriting.me). By accessing or using our text-to-handwriting tools, bulk generators, signature makers, and other pages, you agree to comply with and be bound by the following terms and conditions. If you do not agree, please do not use our services.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary font-mono uppercase tracking-tight">1. Acceptable Use and Forgery Prohibition</h2>
      <p>
        ScribbleCraft is designed to help students, educators, and creative professionals generate realistic handwritten pages and layouts. We enforce a strict policy regarding acceptable use:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1.5">
        <li><strong>Strict Anti-Forgery Policy:</strong> You are strictly prohibited from using our signature generator, cursive fonts, or text-to-handwriting features to forge signatures, copy official document markers, or mimic handwriting styles for fraudulent, deceitful, or malicious purposes.</li>
        <li><strong>Prohibition on Fraudulent Documents:</strong> You must not use our tool to create deceptive legal contracts, invoices, financial records, medical certificates, academic transcripts, or any other official documents meant to mislead third parties.</li>
        <li><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> You agree to use the service only for lawful purposes. You shall not upload images, equations, or texts that violate copyright laws, trademark protections, or the privacy rights of others.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="border-l-2 border-primary pl-4 font-mono text-mute text-xs">
        We reserve the right to suspend or block access to the platform for users suspected of violating these anti-forgery guidelines, and we cooperate fully with authorities in cases of digital forgery or fraudulent activity.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary font-mono uppercase tracking-tight">2. Intellectual Property and Output Ownership</h2>
      <p>
        The ownership of the inputs and outputs on ScribbleCraft is defined as follows:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1.5">
        <li><strong>User Content Ownership:</strong> You retain full copyright and ownership of the text, sketches, formulas, and uploaded images you input into our converter. We do not claim any ownership rights over your documents.</li>
        <li><strong>Exported Document Ownership:</strong> The generated images, PNGs, SVGs, and PDF sheets are 100% yours to download, print, publish, distribute, or license. You can use your exports for commercial, educational, or personal projects without attribution.</li>
        <li><strong>ScribbleCraft Intellectual Property:</strong> All site designs, layout interfaces, canvas rendering scripts, realism algorithms, web worker code, and branding assets remain the exclusive intellectual property of ScribbleCraft and its developers.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary font-mono uppercase tracking-tight">3. Service Availability and Modifications</h2>
      <p>
        While we strive to maintain high availability for our free browser-based tools, we do not guarantee uninterrupted access:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
        <li>We may modify, suspend, or discontinue any feature, font selection, paper preset, or tool page without prior notice.</li>
        <li>Since all canvas compilations and rendering loops occur on your individual browser hardware, site responsiveness is dependent on your local system capacity (memory, browser performance, Web Worker support). We are not responsible for rendering issues on slow devices.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary font-mono uppercase tracking-tight">4. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
      <p>
        THE SERVICE IS PROVIDED ON AN "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE" BASIS. SCRIBBLECRAFT MAKES NO WARRANTIES, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, REGARDING THE ACCURACY, RELIABILITY, OR COMPLETENESS OF GENERATED HANDWRITTEN PAGES, PRINTED PDFS, OR EXPORT STYLES. WE DISCLAIM ALL WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary font-mono uppercase tracking-tight">5. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        IN NO EVENT SHALL SCRIBBLECRAFT, ITS DEVELOPERS, OR ITS AFFILIATES BE LIABLE FOR ANY DIRECT, INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES ARISING OUT OF THE USE OR INABILITY TO USE THE TOOLS, EVEN IF ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH DAMAGES. THIS INCLUDES, BUT IS NOT LIMITED TO, LOSS OF DATA, TRANSCRIBING ERRORS, DEVICE COMPILATION FAILURES, OR ACCUSATIONS OF FORGERY BROUGHT AGAINST YOU.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary font-mono uppercase tracking-tight">6. Governing Law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms and conditions are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of your jurisdiction, without regard to conflict of law principles. Any legal actions or proceedings arising from these terms shall be brought exclusively in the courts located near our headquarters.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary font-mono uppercase tracking-tight">7. Questions and Feedback</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions regarding these terms, please submit a query through our <a href="/contact-us" class="text-link hover:underline">Contact Us</a> page or email <code>support@texttohandwriting.me</code>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <AdSlot slotId="footer-leaderboard" />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
